<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
The molecular phylogeny of 
<bibRefCitation author="Murillo-Ramos, Leidys" journalOrPublisher="PeerJ" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination=": e 7386" refId="B5536902" refString="Murillo-Ramos, Leidys, Brehm, Gunnar, Sihvonen, Pasi, Hausmann, Axel, Holm, Sille, Reza Ghanavi, Hamid, Ounap, Erki, Truuverk, Andro, Staude, Hermann, Friedrich, Egbert, Tammaru, Toomas, Wahlberg, Niklas, 2019. A comprehensive molecular phylogeny of Geometridae (Lepidoptera) with a focus on enigmatic small subfamilies. PeerJ 7: e7386" title="A comprehensive molecular phylogeny of Geometridae (Lepidoptera) with a focus on enigmatic small subfamilies." volume="7" year="2019">Murillo-Ramos et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
indicates that the current concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huebner" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nemoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nemoria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nemoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hübner">Huebner</normalizedToken>
is polyphyletic and that 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. erina" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="species" species="erina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">N. erina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Dognin) and 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. nigrisquama" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="species" species="nigrisquama">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">N. nigrisquama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Dognin) do not belong in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huebner" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nemoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nemoria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nemoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, though there is insufficient evidence to describe new genera or create new combinations for these two species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Brehm, G." journalOrPublisher="Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="457 - 486" refId="B5535732" refString="Brehm, G., Murillo-Ramos, L., Sihvonen, P., Hausmann, A, Schmidt, BC, Ounap, E, Moser, A, Moertter, R, Bolt, D, Bodner, F, Lindt, A, Parra, L, Wahlberg, N, 2019. New World geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae): Molecular phylogeny, biogeography, taxonomic updates and description of 11 new tribes. Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny 77: 457 - 486" title="New World geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae): Molecular phylogeny, biogeography, taxonomic updates and description of 11 new tribes." volume="77" year="2019">Brehm et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
consequently suggested that their generic names are listed in quotation marks, pending further taxonomic study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
In her revision of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huebner" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nemoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nemoria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nemoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitkin, LM" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Natural History Museum (Entomology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="39 - 159" refId="B5536989" refString="Pitkin, LM, 1993. Neotropical emerald moths of the genera Nemoria, Lissochlora and Chavarriella, with particular reference to the species of Costa Rica (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum (Entomology) 62: 39 - 159" title="Neotropical emerald moths of the genera Nemoria, Lissochlora and Chavarriella, with particular reference to the species of Costa Rica (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae)." volume="62" year="1993">Pitkin (1993)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Lissochlora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lissochlora albilineata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albilineata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Lissochlora albilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warren, 1909 to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huebner" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nemoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nemoria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nemoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This new combination, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nemoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nemoria albilineata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albilineata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nemoria albilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Warren, 1909) consequently became a senior homonym of the Texan species 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nemoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nemoria albilineata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albilineata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nemoria albilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cassino, 1927. This homonymy went unnoticed for over a decade, until 
<bibRefCitation author="Kocak, AOe" journalOrPublisher="Miscellaneous papers - Centre for Entomological Studies" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="8 - 9" refId="B5536802" refString="Kocak, AOe, Kemal, M., 2008. Some nomenclatural notes on the Geometridae of the world (Lepidoptera). Miscellaneous papers - Centre for Entomological Studies 138: 8 - 9" title="Some nomenclatural notes on the Geometridae of the world (Lepidoptera)." volume="138" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Koçak">Kocak</normalizedToken>
and Kemal (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
designated a replacement name for the junior homonym.
</paragraph>
